## Database Models (Mongoose)
| Model            | File                        | Key Fields                                                        |
|------------------|-----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|
| User             | lib/models/User.ts          | name, phone, email, password, role, organization                  |
| DonorProfile     | lib/models/User.ts          | user, organization, bloodGroup, district, upazila, isVerified     |
| BloodRequest     | lib/models/BloodRequest.ts  | patientName, bloodGroup, urgency, status, organization            |
| Organization     | lib/models/Organization.ts  | name, slug, primaryColor, isActive                                |
| RiderProfile     | lib/models/RiderProfile.ts  | user, organization, vehicle, status                               |
| DeliveryTask     | lib/models/DeliveryTask.ts  | rider, request, status, pickup/delivery locations                 |
| Donation         | lib/models/Donation.ts      | donor, organization, date, bloodGroup                             |
| Event            | lib/models/Event.ts         | title, organization, date, location                               |
| Feedback         | lib/models/Feedback.ts      | user, organization, message, rating                               |
| AuditLog         | lib/models/AuditLog.ts      | action, user, organization, details                               |
| PushSubscription | lib/models/PushSubscription.ts | user, endpoint, keys                                           |

## User Roles
`donor` | `patient` | `volunteer` | `admin` | `super_admin`

## Blood Groups
`A+` | `A-` | `B+` | `B-` | `O+` | `O-` | `AB+` | `AB-`

## Request Urgency Levels
`normal` | `urgent` | `emergency`

## Request Statuses
`pending` | `fulfilled` | `canceled`

## Key API Routes
| Method | Path                                       | Purpose                       |
|--------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------|
| GET    | /api/donors?orgSlug&bloodGroup&district   | List donors (filtered)        |
| POST   | /api/donors/register                      | Register new donor            |
| POST   | /api/donors/verify                        | Verify/unverify donor (admin) |
| GET    | /api/requests?orgSlug&urgency&status      | List blood requests           |
| POST   | /api/requests/new                         | Create blood request          |
| POST   | /api/requests/status                      | Update request status         |
| GET    | /api/org/stats?orgSlug                    | Org statistics                |
| GET    | /api/org/analytics?orgSlug                | Org analytics data            |
| GET/PUT| /api/org/settings                         | Org settings                  |
| CRUD   | /api/org/users                            | Org user management           |
| CRUD   | /api/admin/organizations                  | Super admin org CRUD          |
| GET    | /api/admin/stats                          | Platform stats                |
| GET    | /api/admin/analytics                      | Platform analytics            |
| CRUD   | /api/riders                               | Rider management              |
| CRUD   | /api/deliveries                           | Delivery task management      |
| CRUD   | /api/events                               | Event management              |
| CRUD   | /api/feedback                             | Feedback management           |
| POST   | /api/push/subscribe                       | Push notification subscribe   |

## Multi-Tenant Architecture
- Organizations identified by URL slug: `/[orgSlug]/...`
- All data (donors, requests) scoped to organization via `organization` ObjectId
- Server-side org lookup: `getOrganizationBySlug(slug)` in `lib/orgUtils.ts`
- Client-side org context: `OrganizationContext` in `lib/context/`
- Dynamic theming via `primaryColor` field

## Environment Variables
| Variable                        | Purpose                           |
|---------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| MONGODB_URI                     | MongoDB connection string         |
| NEXTAUTH_URL                    | Base URL for NextAuth             |
| NEXTAUTH_SECRET                 | JWT signing secret                |
| NEXT_PUBLIC_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY    | Web Push public key               |
| VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY               | Web Push private key              |
| VAPID_SUBJECT                   | Web Push contact mailto           |
| NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED         | Disable Next.js telemetry         |

## Conventions
- **Pages**: `page.tsx` (Next.js App Router convention)
- **Layouts**: `layout.tsx`
- **API Routes**: `route.ts` inside `/api/` directories
- **Components**: PascalCase filenames (e.g., `Navbar.tsx`)
- **Utilities**: camelCase filenames (e.g., `orgUtils.ts`)
- **Models**: PascalCase filenames (e.g., `User.ts`)
- **DB Connection**: Always call `await connectToDatabase()` from `@/lib/db/mongodb` before queries
- **Validation**: Use Zod schemas for form/API input validation
- **State**: React useState/useEffect for client state; MongoDB for persistence
- **Auth checks**: Use `getServerSession(authOptions)` for server-side auth
- **Toasts**: Use `toast.success()` / `toast.error()` from `sonner`
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 utility classes; custom `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` via `cn()` helper

## Scripts
| Command              | Purpose                        |
|----------------------|--------------------------------|
| `npm run dev`        | Dev server (Turbopack)         |
| `npm run build`      | Production build               |
| `npm run start`      | Production server              |
| `npm run lint`       | ESLint                         |
| `npx tsx scripts/seed.ts` | Seed DB with test data    |

## Known TODOs / Tech Debt
1. Password hashing needs bcrypt in production (demo bypass exists)
2. No root `middleware.ts` for route protection
3. SMS/OTP verification not connected to real gateway
4. `villagesCovered` stat is hardcoded to 45
5. Some stats return mock string fallbacks instead of 0
6. District/Upazila inputs could use standardized dropdown data
7. Session type uses `(session.user as any)` in places
8. Push notifications for emergency requests need completion
